stimulus:
Consent form

In this study, you will have to complete two questionnaires and two tasks.

The questionnaires are about your daily psychological functioning, and the tasks are two games to measure your association skills and sensitivity to visual illusions.

The questionnaires and tasks must be completed alone. Your participation is confidential and your answers will be anonymized. We do not collect your IP address or any other identifying information.

Your data are very valuable to us. In participating, you will contribute to scientific progress. In participating, you accept to follow the instructions and to supply honest answers. You can also refuse to partake without any justification and with absolutely no consequences.

If you don't want to participate, or if you want to leave the study, you can simply close your browser.

The entire study takes approximately 40 minutes, with questionnaires in between parts of the tasks. Please, stay focused until the screen confirming that your data are saved appears.


If you have any questions regarding the study, you can email Baptiste Fauvel (baptiste.fauvel@u-paris.fr). This study has been reviewed and approved by the ethical committee of the University of Paris .
Have you ever been diagnosed with any of the following pathologies ?
Are you currently diagnosed with any of the following pathologies ?
Do you meditate regularly? E.g. at least once a week?
Have you taken a psychedelic during the last month? (E.g. LSD, psilocybin mushrooms, ayahuasca)

Shape-Label Association Game

In this task, you will be shown some shapes that will be assigned to a label (You, Your Best Friend and a Stranger).

To personalize this game to your own experience, you will first select who you want the friend and the stranger to be.

Practice

Each label (i.e., You, Best Friend, Stranger) will be assigned to a specific shape (circle, square or triangle)

During the practice phase, you will be presented with one of the shapes above a fixation cross, together with the three labels below the fixation cross.

Your task is to select the label that corresponds with the presented shape as quickly and accurately as possible

If the correct label is on the left, press 'v'.

If the correct label is in the middle, press 'b'.

If the correct label is on the right, press 'n'.

Illusion Game

In this game of speed and reflex, you will need to make visual judgments (for instance, which circle is the biggest, or which line is the longest), as fast and as correctly as possible, while resisting different visual illusions.

We are going to start with some examples of all the illusions you will encounter in the game.

Practice

In this part, two red circles will appear side by side on the screen.

Your task is to select which red circle is bigger in size as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the surrounding black circles around the red circles!

Press the LEFT or the RIGHT arrow to indicate which is the bigger red circle.

In this example, the correct answer is the LEFT arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Training Completed

In the next phase, there will be more trials, and some might be harder too.
Moreover, after each illusion block, a score will be calculated based on speed (time you took to answer) and accuracy (number of errors).

Try to keep up a high score!


Note that it can be really challenging at times, so you will need to rely on your intuition and gut feeling to answer as fast as you can without making errors.

Each illusion block will be repeated two times (so that you have the opportunity to improve your score), but the order of the blocks is random.

Remember, your goal is to be as fast and accurate as possible. Good luck!
